      Dept. of Information Security and Communication Technology
repository-code: 'https://github.com/dryuemco/industrial_robot_security'
url: 'https://www.enfield-project.eu/'
abstract: >-
  A formal adversarial testing framework for detecting safety
  and security violations in industrial robot code generated by
  Large Language Models. Combines ISO 10218:2025 safety analysis
  with CWE-based security checks and adversarial prompt injection
  testing (A6.1-A6.8). Includes a vendor-neutral Task IR format
  (15 baseline tasks across 5 categories and 3 operating modes),
  an attack variant generator producing 120 adversarial variants
  (8 attack types A1-A8), an AST-based static watchdog with
  safety rules (DM-1..7) and security rules (SM-1..7) achieving
  95% detection rate at 0% false positives, an LLM code generation
  client supporting Qwen2.5-Coder-32B, Qwen 3.5 27B, and CodeLlama-34B via Ollama for
  multi-model comparison, an IR-to-URScript translator for UR5e,
  and runtime safety monitors for ROS2 Humble simulation
  environments. Simulation-only — no physical robot deployment.
keywords:
  - adversarial-testing
  - llm-safety
  - llm-security
  - industrial-robots
  - iso-10218
  - ros2
  - ast-analysis
  - robot-security
  - prompt-injection
  - cwe
  - code-generation
